reasoning: Grade 1 (low-grade) NET represents ~25-30% of all NETs. Global NET incidence estimated 2-5 per 100k, with grade 1 representing lower end at ~2.5 per 100k.
source: Yao JC et al. (2008). One hundred years after 'carcinoid': epidemiology of and prognostic factors for neuroendocrine tumors in 35,825 cases in the United States. J Clin Oncol. 26(18):3063-3072
